<subSubSection pageId="66" pageNumber="67" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,1635,1947]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1635,1660]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1914" box="[493,716,1636,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosana">
<emphasis box="[493,716,1636,1660]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Rhotana formosana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group can be recognized by the combination of the following characters:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,1635,1947]" box="[151,977,1708,1732]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">1. Hindwings with small black mark(s) around base(s) of Ms2 and Ms1.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,1635,1947]" box="[151,929,1743,1767]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">2. Forewings with anterior apical crossveins lined with dark stripes.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,1635,1947]" box="[151,929,1780,1804]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">3. Forewings with Ms1 fork distad of apex of the basal median cell.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,1635,1947]" box="[151,805,1815,1840]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">4. Facial carinae contiguous until lower margins of eyes.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,1635,1947]" box="[151,747,1852,1876]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">5. Male pygofer usually without lateral projections.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
